1) TOG-ETB Organization 

There are five tools identified in the MedSecurance toolbox-planning spreadsheet:
TOG-ETB Assurance Tool
TOG-ETB CAP Renderer
TOG-ETB Knowledge Base
TOG-ETB Evidence Repository
TOG-ETB Tool Agent

This directory contains numerous subdirectories, listed below, containing sources,
repository, knowledge base, build and test facilities, and generated Certification
Assurance Packages (CAPs). Among them are directories and files associated with the
above listed tools (as indicated within parentheses).

BUILD - build/deploy the executable tools
CAP - Certification Assurance Package (TOG-ETB CAP Renderer)
docs - design, developer, and user documentation
KB - knowledge base of MODELS, PATTERNS, ... (TOG-ETB Knowledge Base)
KB - knowledge base (TOG-ETB Knowledge Base, TOG-ETB Assurance Tool)
	system models (TOG-ETB Assurance Tool)
	assurance case patterns (TOG-ETB Assurance Tool)
	/ MODELS / <version> / policy.pl, platform.pl, configuration.pl, ...
                             / properties / p1.pro ...
	/ PATTERNS / patterns.pl
REPOSITORY - generated files for assurance CASES and EVIDENCE
	assurance case repository - (TOG-ETB Assurance Tool)
	evidence repository - (TOG-ETB Assurance Tool and TOG-ETB Evidence Repository)
	/ CASES / <case> / repository.pl (* generated *)
	/ EVIDENCE / repository.pl (* generated *)
                   / <category> / <xref> / status, aargs, ... (* generated *)
RUNTIME - temporary and persistent runtime files
src - source code, including subdirectories
	agents - (TOG-ETB Tool Agent)
	com - common and configuration files
		command.pl, param.pl, procs.pl, test.pl, ui.pl,
	tog_etb.pl, command_etb.pl, demo.pl. etb.pl, evidence.pl, export.pl, instantiate.pl
	models_api - internal APIs to access models
	/ models_api / common.pl, policy.pl, platform.pl, configuration.pl, model.pl
	...
TEST - test scripts and test cases


