4) Evidence validation: the big picture

- every new evidence artefact
  -- is registered in the evidence database as 'pending'
  -- gets assigned a working repository (category/xref) 
  -- gets assigned a status file in the working repository (status)
  -- the status file is initialized to contain 'pending'
  -- an agent is launched for it 

- every launched agents works 'synchronously' as follows:
  -- call external tools and/or update the content of the repository 
  -- returns the validation status amongst 'ongoing', 'valid', 'invalid'
  -- ongoing denotes that no answer can be provided right now
     (e.g, may need user interaction, etc)
  
- on agent return for an evidence artefact 
  -- its status in the evidence repository is updated
  -- the status file in the working directory is updated 
     [ both will contain the returned validation status ]

- for evidence checking marked as 'ongoing'
  -- the validation continue 'asynchronously' (wrt the AM-ETB)
  -- the working directory can be updated, etc
  -- once a definite verdict 'valid' / 'invalid' is reached
     it shall be written in the status file

- AM-ETB has a re-synchronization action that updates the status of all
  ongoing activities depending on the content of the status file
  (evidence:update_ongoing)

